narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Obviously is you're an ER&M major you have to take it. It is an interesting course and had great guest speakers. Good exposure to different kinds of scholarship out there.

A good chance to meet your fellow ER&M majors. A good opportunity to think about yourself as a scholar and the choices you will make while writing your senior essay. A good opportunity to begin thinking about your senior essay. Sometimes the readings felt like things you may have read in Intro ER&M, but hopefully you can gear the discussion towards what you would find most helpful to talk about.
It's a good course--solid reading and you get to hang out with your fellow majors. I don't see why you would take it if you weren't an ER&M major though.
BE AN ER&M MAJOR! Therefore, you have to take this and it is worth it.
